			<div class="content" id="post-content-2064812">
									

<p>Well, Victim-011 repeatedly refers to the subject as &quot;her&quot; - perhaps the incident report was prepared by a female agent?</p>
<p>Notes on article: Typo at the beginning of the interview, where the interview subject is referred to as Victom-011. Also, I would recommend replacing the word &quot;slime&quot; with &quot;mucus&quot;, as this is more properly descriptive of a snail's secretions. Other than that, stellar work, and it's nice to see that the UIU doesn't always come in second when securing a subject.</p>

